reviews.review_text:
Dane Co. I saw nearly every show here, and they always played really well at this venue. The sound was always dialed in, Always GA, and I don’t remember the place ever being  sold out. I think it held 8-9000, but there was always room, especially in the bleachers, as most people crowded the floor.
A great audience tape that puts you right there.
‘78 gets a bad rap, but through July at least, there were many hot shows, with numerous songs that “peaked” this year. Loser, Peggy -O, Music, BE Women versions from this night are about as good as these songs were ever played.
